Inspired by activism of CO students taking a stand against gun violence. 

“School is supposed to be a place where you go to take the next steps into your life…not a place where all of that is taken away in seconds" -Chaparral HS student Cassidy Ramsey

We must take action now.

Today’s indictments again prove that Putin interfered in 2016 election. There's no good explanation for why admin hasn’t imposed a single sanction for election interference. @POTUS must stop taking Putin’s denials at face value & work to deter future interference in our democracy
WATCH: Live now on the Daily Briefing with @danaperino & @SenCoryGardner to discuss the immigration debate unfolding in the Senate
TUNE IN this morning: Getting ready to speak with @morningmika & @JoeNBC on @Morning_Joe.

When did mass shootings become a normal part of American life? There's an entire generation growing up in fear that their school will be next.  My thoughts are with families of victims & first responders in FL, but I also know that thoughts are not enough. It's time for action.

A good reminder from Frederick Douglass on his 200th birthday: "Principles contained in [the Declaration of Independence] are saving principles. Stand by those principles, be true to them on all occasions, in all places, against all foes, and at whatever cost.” #BlackHistoryMonth

As the Senate begins debate this week on an immigration bill, we must remember what’s at stake: protecting the hundreds of thousands of #Dreamers who are about to lose their status because of @POTUS’ decision to rescind the #DACA program.

After $1.5 trillion in tax cuts for people who don’t need them & hundreds of billions more put on the nation’s credit card with last week’s budget agreement–the #TrumpBudget makes it clear who will pick up the tab: Rural Coloradans & our kids and grandkids.

Thank you to all of the Dreamers, advocates & Coloradans who have not stopped working for one minute to ensure we keep families together in this country. We continue to carry your voices into every meeting with Senate colleagues to find a solution. We won’t stop fighting for you.
Looking forward to another bipartisan meeting tomorrow on DACA/Dream with Senators Graham, Flake, Durbin, and others. Continuing to work together to find a solution to protect #Dreamers.

#PaidLeaveMeans eliminating the false choice between work & family. Since #FMLA25, we’ve made progress. But it’s been 25 years & it’s time to take next steps to ensure Coloradans have the security & peace of mind they deserve.
Only this President could make a call for unity sound so divisive.

THREAD: Ahead of tonight’s #SOTU, I’m sharing the comments you’ve sent on Twitter, FB, email, and over the phone about the important issues you'd like to hear in tonight's address. Our priorities for the next year should be shaped by the #VoicesOfCO. 1/x

“We sought justice because equal pay for equal work is an American value.” – Lilly Ledbetter
On 9th anniversary of Lily Ledbetter Fair Pay Act, we celebrate progress made & recognize work still to do. Let's ensure our laws align w/ ideals & eliminate pay discrimination for good.

What do you want to hear in tomorrow’s State of the Union? Share the issues that are important to you with hashtag #VoicesOfCO. 

Tomorrow, I’ll be sharing the vision that I want to hear in the #SOTU, and I want input from Coloradans as we look to priorities for the year ahead.

Later today, the Senate is voting on a 20-week abortion ban, jeopardizing a woman’s right to make her own healthcare decisions. I have voted against this measure in the past, and I will do so again. #NoAbortionBan

FBI Deputy Director McCabe is a public servant, and @POTUS’ attacks on him undermine our democratic institutions. 

FBI investigations should be entirely free from political influence or intimidation. The independence of the agency is critical to the rule of law.

This wkd, reflected on my family’s history surviving the Holocaust, while at the same time seeing troubling headlines in France & Poland that remind us anti-semitism is very much alive. Now more than ever, #WeRemember & commit to this never happening again. #HolocaustMemorialDay

Last night’s news reaffirms that the American people deserve the truth about Putin’s attempts to influence 2016 election & any possible collusion. We will continue to do everything to protect the rule of law. The investigation must continue without interference or interruption.

Due to the government shutdown, our office is operating at reduced capacity. Our focus continues to be responding to the needs & concerns of Coloradans. If you contact us, we'll do our best to reply in a timely manner. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.
From @ChiefPentSpox: CR’s “are wasteful, they're destructive, and the longer they go the worse it is.” We should stay in Washington to do our jobs & negotiate a real budget.
Happening soon: Tune into @NPR's Morning Edition where we'll be talking about the bipartisan #DACA deal
Just finished speaking on the Senate floor with my colleagues. We should not leave Washington until we pass a solution for #Dreamers.

The President should spend less time disparaging @SenatorDurbin and more time working with the Democrats and Republicans who put forth a #DACA deal that included everything he requested. It’s past time for us to pass a deal to protect Dreamers.

Our bipartisan #DACA deal is not “dead.” Democrats and Republicans negotiated in good faith and came to an agreement that protects Dreamers and increases border security. We’ll keep working to build support for this deal. I urge my colleagues to join me in doing the right thing.
.@POTUS must apologize for his abhorrent comments. We are a nation of immigrants; it’s what makes us strong.
“Give me your tired, your poor, your huddled masses yearning to breathe free.”

Taking a moment tonight on #LawEnforcementAppreciationDay to think of all the brave law enforcement officers across Colorado. Thank you for working tirelessly day in and day out to keep our communities safe.

To the extent the WH meeting helped narrow the scope of negotiations & prioritize #DreamAct, this was a positive first step. I'm pleased there seemed to be acknowledgement of urgent need to pass a bipartisan bill, so DACA recipients stop losing status & having their lives upended

The SAFER Act was signed into law today—bipartisan legislation that will help reduce the nationwide rape kit backlog. This progress puts us one step closer to ensuring survivors of sexual violence receive the thorough and fair investigations they deserve.

Introduced legislation earlier this year to ensure legal #marijuana businesses can access banking services. AG Sessions’ actions yesterday will make this even more difficult and may raise significant public safety issues.  Another reason why DOJ must rescind #marijuana guidance.
As of today, 14,586 Dreamers have lost their DACA status. Finding a bipartisan solution for Dreamers should be a top priority on our first day back in session in the new year. #DreamActNOW

As the Senate comes back in session today, we are as determined as ever to stand up for Colorado's families. Starting the year off fighting for #CHIP, #DACA, #NetNeutrality, #CHCs, a government funding bill, and more.
2018 is going to be another eventful year. Spent today with family & thinking about the important work we have ahead of us. Wishing you all a Happy New Year!
Grateful for the bravery of our law enforcement in Douglas County. ​Our prayers are with the families of the deputy who was killed and the other officers injured in the line of duty.

Last week, oil companies had the chance to bid on 10.3 million acres open for drilling in Alaska. In the end, less than 1% of the land was leased. 
We’re not even using all of the land now available for drilling. It defies reason that we would open up even more. #ProtectTheArctic

The House just passed #GOPTaxBill that will increase our nation’s debt by $1.4 trillion. For the same cost, we could provide funding for #opioidcrisis, #EarlyChildhoodEducation, #cleanenergy R&D, #affordablehousing, #infrastructure, & more. 

Which plan do you prefer?
hashtags: GOPTaxBill opioidcrisis EarlyChildhoodEducation cleanenergy affordablehousing infrastructure

text: One topic noticeably missing from #NationalSecurityStrategy: Climate change. Bipartisan group of lawmakers have acknowledged #climatechange as a national security threat. @POTUS silence is cause for serious concern.

#SandyHook—an unspeakable tragedy—should never be normal condition of American life, yet it’s 5 yrs later & we’ve taken no action. We cannot lose belief that it’s within our power to protect our kids at a school—or night club or concert. It’s well past time to #HonorWithAction.
#GOPTaxBill Conference Committee: Throw out the #ArcticRider. It is shortsighted, expensive, and deeply unpopular. We should protect our greatest national treasure, not exploit it. #ProtectTheArctic

Then-Maj Leader @SenatorReid said in 2010: "We’re going to wait until the new senator [Republican Scott Brown] arrives until we do anything more on health care." It was the right thing to do. We should follow suit & wait to vote on #GOPTaxBill until Sen-Elect Doug Jones is seated
Welcome to the Senate, Doug Jones.

For people in Colorado, health care is about caring for a sick child or an aging parent. It has nothing to do with politics. It's not too late for @SenateGOP to work on bipartisan #taxreform that would not strip millions of health coverage.
76 years after the attack on Pearl Harbor, we honor the legacy of the Greatest Generation that fought to protect the freedoms we cherish today. These brave men & women will never be forgotten.
Sexual harassment and misconduct are never acceptable. I understand Senator Franken will make an announcement tomorrow morning, and I'm confident he'll do the right thing and step aside.
As #GOPTaxBill works its way through conference, it’s worth noting again that there are bipartisan issues on which GOP & Dems could work together to bring real tax reform to Coloradans.

With @POTUS announcement today to diminish #BearsEars & #GrandStaircase, he explicitly:
1. Disregarded wishes of tribes
2. Ignored overwhelming public comments from Western leaders
3. Dismissed @USDA guidance regarding @forestservice lands
Offered amendment with @SenSherrodBrown to increase #ChildTaxCredit. We could cut child poverty nearly in half and strengthen middle-class families, but #GOPTaxBill misses the mark.

RT if you agree we should scrap this #GOPTaxBill. 
RT if you think we should hold at least a single hearing with input from experts. 
RT if you believe tax reform that will affect our entire economy should be bipartisan.
.@POTUS’ retweets of an extremist hate group are irresponsible and disgraceful. Hate groups should be condemned, not promoted.
TUNE IN: Speaking live with @chucktodd to discuss why we must scrap this partisan #GOPTaxPlan & work together to create responsible, bipartisan tax reform. #MTPDaily

This year, @SenateGOP tried 4 separate times to repeal the ACA and replace it with a proposal to cut taxes for those w/ yearly incomes over $1 million & slash health care for most vulnerable. We stopped them then, and we must stop them again this week.
Every day, more #Dreamers are losing DACA protections & put at risk of deportation. We must #ProtectDreamers & pass the #DreamAct before the end of the year.

While GOP is trying to slash taxes at top & leave our kids to foot the bill, intro’d amendment to lower #HigherEd costs by:
-increasing tax credit for college by $500/year
-eliminating taxes on Pell Grants
-exempting AmeriCorps award b/c taxes shouldn't be a barrier to education

In the late hours of last night, @GOPSenFinance jammed a tax plan through committee that will cut taxes for Americans making more than $1 million/yr & leave our kids to foot the bill. 

This is not over yet. We have to stop this terribly misguided legislation.
Just now in @SenateFinance: Aside from @ChuckGrassley, @POTUS administration & GOP experts refused to commit to keep tax credit extensions for wind & solar energy in #GOPTaxPlan.

Today we honor the invaluable contributions of our veterans & reaffirm our commitment to support them & their families. In Colorado, we strive to make our state the best place for veterans to live & work. Thankful for our brave men & women this #VeteransDay & everyday.

It is 1:30 ET on Thursday afternoon and we have not seen the GOP tax plan. We have not had a single hearing. Not a single economist has given their opinion. This is not the way to legislate. Every hour that goes by is one more hour Americans are not getting the truth.
Even Syria will join #ParisAgreement. This doesn't make America great. It makes us the only country denying the reality of #climatechange.
Devastating news of another mass shooting. Our hearts are w/ victims in TX. Americans should not live in fear of gun violence. We must act.
Waiting for more information, but praying for the victims of tonight's shooting in Thornton. Thank you to all the first responders.
45,000 Coloradans rely on the #CSR payments that @POTUS ripped away. #AlexanderMurray is a bipartisan way to fix this chaos.
Applaud @SenAlexander @PattyMurray on bipartisan agreement to help stabilize indiv insurance market. This is path forward—not Trump sabotage
As father of 3 daughters, thinking of all girls around world who deserve equal rights & empowerment to reach full potential. #DayoftheGirl

Devastating news. Our hearts go out to all of the victims and their families in Las Vegas.

Must continue bipartisan work to stabilize ind insurance market. This is path forward—not #GrahamCassidy that would strip 32mil of coverage.
Heading to our first bipartisan #healthcare hearing in the HELP Committee. Ready to work to find ways to lower costs for Coloradans.
North Korea poses a grave threat to our nation's security and to global stability and norms. 1/2

Ready to work with Senate colleagues on real tax reform that benefits all Americans. (2/2)
#TaxReform should cut taxes for lower and middle income families and not add to our national debt. This is common sense. (1/2)
Celebrating the anniversary of women’s suffrage on #WomensEqualityDay & committing to fight until we achieve full equality.
Thinking of the sailors and families of the USS John S. McCain. Praying for the safety of the missing sailors.
We strongly condemn the horrific attack in Barcelona & stand by Spain, our European ally. Our thoughts are with the victims & their families

Today's attack is not the result of “many sides”— it's an act of domestic terrorism. @POTUS should explicitly denounce white supremacy.
The events in VA are contrary to all we stand for as a country. Embrace inclusion, celebrate differences—that's the America we believe in.
NK is racing to pursue destabilizing & dangerous nucle​ar program, which threatens our security, including personnel, partners, and allies.
#Startups create good jobs, especially in CO. Let's work to support their innovation so we can grow our economy. #StartupDay
No party—Republican or Democrat—has the votes to fix healthcare alone. Bipartisanship is the only way forward. Now the real work begins.
Grateful to @SenJohnMcCain for his vote last night and his call for a bipartisan process.
As a father, I'm grateful for the example @lisamurkowski & @SenatorCollins set for my daughters. Thanks for standing strong throughout.

-269K lose coverage
-avg annual premiums up $751
-uncompensated care for hospitals up $242M

Unacceptable.

Voted against #Trumpcare repeal & replace that would cost 22 mil people health care. We're still fighting any repeal & won't be discouraged.
Thank you @SenJohnMcCain for your call to work together. The loudest partisan voices should not drive our debate.
It’s shameful that @SenateGOP just voted to take up unknown legislation that could harm millions of Coloradans and Americans.
We're counting on Bernhardt to uphold his commitment to protect CO’s forward-leaning methane rules & ensure we're not put at a disadvantage.
My prayers are with @SenJohnMcCain as he battles through this. This American hero is as tough as they come.
#DACA has opened doors and opportunities for over 17,000 DREAMers in CO, and by extension for all of their families. We must #defendDACA.
The internet was built to be open and free. We should work together to protect #NetNeutrality
On this #IndependenceDay, we celebrate our democracy and our institutions that make it possible.
Wishing everyone in Colorado and across the country a happy #July4. Thank you to all who serve and protect our great nation.
Renewable energy is critical for energy independence. @POTUS #EnergyDominance speech is smoke & mirrors to distract from devastating DOE cut

Remembering all those who sacrificed for our country. We are forever in their debt & grateful to them & their loved ones. #MemorialDay
